* The universal quantifier ∀x ensures that the statement holds true for any individual x.
* The existential quantifier ∃y means there exists at least one y that satisfies the conditions following the quantifier.
* The Boolean operator ∧ represents logical AND, connecting the two quantifiers and their corresponding statements.
* The statement inside the existential quantifier ensures that there is at least one boy y who has been to Paris and at least one other boy who has been to Paris. It also implies that there is a person z who has been to Paris but is not a boy.
